    {
      "id": 24271,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "On June 28th, @say_ch33se reported that it was possible to bypass Shopify's email verification for legacy accounts. Doing so would have allowed a user to access accounts they did not own. \n\nOur team immediately deployed a change to address this issue. Additionally, we have removed the ability to verify email addresses for legacy accounts. A code to confirm email ownership at the time of merging from a legacy account is now required.",
